  <p class="content"><p>Okay, so if I'm understanding the definition of "virtual microscopy", they're looking at an absurdly high-resolution scan of a microscope image, not actively looking through a microscope at a live sample or controlling any microscope directly. Isn't this technically something you could already do with stock software on an MS Surface? It's a neat application of the technology, though.</p>
